## G12 Project Concept enables VS Code–style folder opening with persistent workspace
**Status:** done
**Tags:** stack:backend, module:project
**Depends on:** G7, G9

- [x] Backend SpecsStore starts empty (no auto-load from current_dir)
- [x] Project opens via API: POST /api/forge/project/open with directory path
- [x] Specs auto-discovered from {project}/specs/ with fallback to legacy docs/specs/
- [x] Project config persisted (last project, recent list) in user data dir
- [x] Backend auto-restores last project on restart
- [x] Frontend shows WelcomeView when no project is open
- [x] Path input with directory browsing autocomplete
- [x] Recent projects list for quick re-opening
- [x] Project indicator (name + close button) in navigation rail
- [x] SpecsView and ChatsView use dynamic project from useProject composable
- [x] docs/specs/ promoted to top-level specs/ directory

AutoForge operates on a user-chosen project directory, just like VS Code. On first launch the workspace is empty; the user opens a folder and specs are loaded from its specs/ subdirectory. The last project is remembered across restarts.

## G13 API Source Configuration supports multi-provider LLM management with auto-detection and model tiers
**Status:** in_progress
**Tags:** stack:backend, module:api-sources
**Depends on:** G1, G6

- [ ] ApiSource data model supports Anthropic, OpenAI, and Local providers with per-source models
- [ ] ModelTier enum (Light / Mid / Heavy) maps to concrete models per provider
- [ ] First-startup auto-detection finds existing Claude keys, OpenAI keys, and Ollama instances
- [ ] API sources persisted to `dirs::data_local_dir()/autoforge/api_sources.json`
- [ ] CRUD API endpoints for creating, reading, updating, and deleting API sources
- [ ] Multi-provider AI dispatch routes chat requests to the correct provider (Anthropic SSE, OpenAI streaming, Local/Ollama)
- [ ] API key resolution priority: env var → ~/.claude/settings.json → stored (base64)
- [ ] Test Connection endpoint verifies API source connectivity and credentials
- [ ] APIs top-level view with source list, detail editor, and model management table
- [ ] First-startup UI guides user when no API source is configured

Currently AutoForge only supports Anthropic Claude with a hardcoded API key path. G13 introduces a configurable multi-provider system so agents can use different LLM backends. The APIs view sits as a top-level navigation tab alongside Chat, Specs, and Relay, because Tools and Skills views will follow the same pattern in the future.

## G14 Unified Provider Layer consolidates AI communication from auto-code-rs into provider/ module with SSE streaming
**Status:** done
**Tags:** stack:backend, module:provider
**Depends on:** G1

- [x] Unified message types (ChatMessage, ContentBlock, StreamEvent, ToolChatEvent) in provider/types.rs
- [x] Robust incremental SSE parser (SseParser) in provider/sse.rs handling both \r\n\r\n and \n\n delimiters
- [x] Single ClaudeProvider with chat_stream() and chat_turn() methods replacing both ai.rs and forge/ai.rs
- [x] ToolError enum (ExecutionFailed, InvalidInput, PermissionDenied) for structured tool error handling
- [x] ContextManager with token estimation and automatic compaction
- [x] Session persistence in JSONL format at ~/.autoforge/sessions/
- [x] PermissionPolicy with Allow/Ask/ReadOnly modes

The provider/ module is the unified AI communication layer, ported from auto-code-rs and merged with auto-forge's existing Claude integration. It replaces both the old ai.rs and forge/ai.rs modules, providing a single entry point for all LLM interactions with structured types and robust SSE parsing.

